coffin_description "As you step into Sombra's coffin, you are transported to an enchanted realm of eternal night.  Gazing up at the starlitheavens, it takes you a second to realize you are actuallylooking through glass.  You're standing in a large room walled in glass.  In each corner of the room, a crystalfireplace adds light to this surreal place, casting dancingshadows across a white marbled floor.  You suddenly begin tonotice the furnishings in the room and are surpriesed at howstarkly they contrast with their surroundings.Nearest you is a reading area consisting of an overstuffed,black leather sofa and two matching chairs.  An obsidiancoffee table sits between them and an impressive library ofbooks lines the walls in waist high shelves.Tearing yourself away from the library, you notice that a huge four-poster, mahogany bed seated on a Ming Dynasty ruglies across the room.  The bed seems out of place in thisenchanted realm, almost a flashback to what once was, yet itseems to fit perfectly in some odd way.Finally, in a small alcove off to the right, you notice..."
